{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm going to talk to you about some stuff\nthat's in this book of mine"},{"time":3310,"text":"that I hope will resonate with other\nthings you've already heard,"},{"time":6431,"text":"and I'll try to make\nsome connections myself,"},{"time":8756,"text":"in case you missed them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10100,"text":"But I want to start with\nwhat I call the \"official dogma.\""},{"time":14936,"text":"The official dogma of what?"},{"time":16412,"text":"The official dogma of all Western\nindustrial societies."},{"time":19742,"text":"And the official dogma runs like this:"},{"time":22079,"text":"if we are interested in maximizing\nthe welfare of our citizens,"},{"time":26801,"text":"the way to do that\nis to maximize individual freedom."},{"time":32892,"text":"The reason for this is both that freedom\nis in and of itself good,"},{"time":37000,"text":"valuable, worthwhile,\nessential to being human."},{"time":40519,"text":"And because if people have freedom,"},{"time":43000,"text":"then each of us can act on our own"},{"time":45000,"text":"to do the things\nthat will maximize our welfare,"},{"time":47310,"text":"and no one has to decide on our behalf."},{"time":50698,"text":"The way to maximize freedom\nis to maximize choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55738,"text":"The more choice people have,\nthe more freedom they have,"},{"time":59452,"text":"and the more freedom they have,"},{"time":61159,"text":"the more welfare they have."},{"time":64000,"text":"This, I think, is so deeply embedded\nin the water supply"},{"time":69000,"text":"that it wouldn't occur\nto anyone to question it."},{"time":73295,"text":"And it's also deeply\nembedded in our lives."},{"time":77648,"text":"I'll give you some examples"},{"time":79336,"text":"of what modern progress\nhas made possible for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"This is my supermarket."},{"time":84830,"text":"Not such a big one."},{"time":86840,"text":"I want to say just a word\nabout salad dressing."},{"time":89263,"text":"175 salad dressings in my supermarket,"},{"time":92000,"text":"if you don't count the 10\nextra-virgin olive oils"},{"time":95000,"text":"and 12 balsamic vinegars you could buy"},{"time":98000,"text":"to make a very large number\nof your own salad dressings,"},{"time":101000,"text":"in the off-chance that none of the 175\nthe store has on offer suit you."},{"time":106476,"text":"So this is what the supermarket is like."},{"time":108437,"text":"And then you go\nto the consumer electronics store"},{"time":110889,"text":"to set up a stereo system --"},{"time":112508,"text":"speakers, CD player,\ntape player, tuner, amplifier --"},{"time":116000,"text":"and in this one single\nconsumer electronics store,"},{"time":120000,"text":"there are that many stereo systems."},{"time":123920,"text":"We can construct six-and-a-half-million\ndifferent stereo systems"},{"time":128921,"text":"out of the components\nthat are on offer in one store."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131603,"text":"You've got to admit\nthat's a lot of choice."},{"time":134294,"text":"In other domains --\nthe world of communications."},{"time":138389,"text":"There was a time, when I was a boy,"},{"time":140255,"text":"when you could get any kind\nof telephone service you wanted,"},{"time":143096,"text":"as long as it came from Ma Bell."},{"time":144938,"text":"You rented your phone. You didn't buy it."},{"time":147000,"text":"One consequence of that, by the way,\nis that the phone never broke."},{"time":150215,"text":"And those days are gone."},{"time":153000,"text":"We now have an almost\nunlimited variety of phones,"},{"time":156000,"text":"especially in the world of cell phones."},{"time":158000,"text":"These are cell phones of the future."},{"time":161000,"text":"My favorite is the middle one --"},{"time":163000,"text":"the MP3 player, nose hair trimmer,\nand crème brûlée torch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167209,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":169720,"text":"And if by some chance you haven't\nseen that in your store yet,"},{"time":173000,"text":"you can rest assured\nthat one day soon, you will."},{"time":175910,"text":"And what this does"},{"time":177111,"text":"is it leads people to walk\ninto their stores asking this question."},{"time":180785,"text":"And do you know what the answer\nto this question now is?"},{"time":183477,"text":"The answer is \"no.\""},{"time":185516,"text":"It is not possible to buy a cell phone\nthat doesn't do too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189578,"text":"So, in other aspects of life that are much\nmore significant than buying things,"},{"time":194000,"text":"the same explosion of choice is true."},{"time":197517,"text":"Health care."},{"time":199047,"text":"It is no longer the case\nin the United States"},{"time":201604,"text":"that you go to the doctor,\nand the doctor tells you what to do."},{"time":205480,"text":"Instead, you go to the doctor,"},{"time":207163,"text":"and the doctor tells you,\n\"Well, we could do A, or we could do B."},{"time":210337,"text":"A has these benefits, and these risks."},{"time":212743,"text":"B has these benefits, and these risks."},{"time":215375,"text":"What do you want to do?\""},{"time":217138,"text":"And you say, \"Doc, what should I do?\""},{"time":220000,"text":"And the doc says, \"A has\nthese benefits and risks,"},{"time":222780,"text":"and B has these benefits and risks."},{"time":224762,"text":"What do you want to do?\""},{"time":226777,"text":"And you say, \"If you were me,\nDoc, what would you do?\""},{"time":230793,"text":"And the doc says, \"But I'm not you.\""},{"time":234000,"text":"And the result is --\nwe call it \"patient autonomy,\""},{"time":236842,"text":"which makes it sound like a good thing,"},{"time":238739,"text":"but it really is a shifting\nof the burden and the responsibility"},{"time":241826,"text":"for decision-making from somebody\nwho knows something --"},{"time":244499,"text":"namely, the doctor --"},{"time":245537,"text":"to somebody who knows nothing\nand is almost certainly sick"},{"time":248293,"text":"and thus not in the best shape\nto be making decisions --"},{"time":251000,"text":"namely, the patient."},{"time":252896,"text":"There's enormous marketing\nof prescription drugs"},{"time":255746,"text":"to people like you and me,"},{"time":257021,"text":"which, if you think about it,\nmakes no sense at all,"},{"time":259501,"text":"since we can't buy them."},{"time":260738,"text":"Why do they market to us\nif we can't buy them?"},{"time":263215,"text":"The answer is that they expect us\nto call our doctors the next morning"},{"time":267000,"text":"and ask for our prescriptions\nto be changed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270532,"text":"Something as dramatic as our identity"},{"time":274533,"text":"has now become a matter of choice,"},{"time":277317,"text":"as this slide is meant to indicate."},{"time":280794,"text":"We don't inherit an identity;\nwe get to invent it."},{"time":283646,"text":"And we get to re-invent\nourselves as often as we like."},{"time":287000,"text":"And that means that every day,\nwhen you wake up in the morning,"},{"time":289977,"text":"you have to decide what kind\nof person you want to be."},{"time":293721,"text":"With respect to marriage and family,"},{"time":297444,"text":"there was a time when the default\nassumption that almost everyone had"},{"time":302289,"text":"is that you got married\nas soon as you could,"},{"time":304415,"text":"and then you started having kids\nas soon as you could."},{"time":307049,"text":"The only real choice was who,"},{"time":309928,"text":"not when, and not what you did after."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313112,"text":"Nowadays, everything\nis very much up for grabs."},{"time":316000,"text":"I teach wonderfully intelligent students,"},{"time":318745,"text":"and I assign 20 percent\nless work than I used to."},{"time":322543,"text":"And it's not because they're less smart,"},{"time":325000,"text":"and it's not because\nthey're less diligent."},{"time":327417,"text":"It's because they are preoccupied,\nasking themselves,"},{"time":330894,"text":"\"Should I get married or not?\nShould I get married now?"},{"time":333530,"text":"Should I get married later?"},{"time":334847,"text":"Should I have kids first,\nor a career first?\""},{"time":337258,"text":"All of these are consuming questions."},{"time":340000,"text":"And they're going to answer\nthese questions,"},{"time":342120,"text":"whether or not it means\nnot doing all the work I assign"},{"time":344765,"text":"and not getting a good grade\nin my courses."},{"time":346843,"text":"And indeed they should."},{"time":348001,"text":"These are important questions to answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351887,"text":"Work --"},{"time":353074,"text":"we are blessed, as Carl was pointing out,"},{"time":355393,"text":"with the technology that enables us"},{"time":357394,"text":"to work every minute of every day\nfrom any place on the planet --"},{"time":363460,"text":"except the Randolph Hotel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365777,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":368841,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370634,"text":"There is one corner, by the way,"},{"time":373000,"text":"that I'm not going to tell anybody about,\nwhere the WiFi actually works."},{"time":377630,"text":"I'm not telling you about it\nbecause I want to use it."},{"time":380439,"text":"So what this means,"},{"time":381708,"text":"this incredible freedom of choice\nwe have with respect to work,"},{"time":384771,"text":"is that we have to make a decision,"},{"time":386468,"text":"again and again and again,"},{"time":388580,"text":"about whether we should\nor shouldn't be working."},{"time":391000,"text":"We can go to watch our kid play soccer,"},{"time":393629,"text":"and we have our cell phone on one hip,"},{"time":395630,"text":"and our Blackberry on our other hip,"},{"time":397701,"text":"and our laptop, presumably, on our laps."},{"time":400435,"text":"And even if they're all shut off,"},{"time":402571,"text":"every minute that we're watching\nour kid mutilate a soccer game,"},{"time":405666,"text":"we are also asking ourselves,"},{"time":407472,"text":"\"Should I answer this cell phone call?"},{"time":409522,"text":"Should I respond to this email?\nShould I draft this letter?\""},{"time":412419,"text":"And even if the answer\nto the question is \"no,\""},{"time":415000,"text":"it's certainly going to make\nthe experience of your kid's soccer game"},{"time":418310,"text":"very different than it would've been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":420666,"text":"So everywhere we look,"},{"time":422731,"text":"big things and small things,\nmaterial things and lifestyle things,"},{"time":426513,"text":"life is a matter of choice."},{"time":429444,"text":"And the world we used\nto live in looked like this."},{"time":433000,"text":"[Well, actually,\nthey are written in stone.]"},{"time":435235,"text":"That is to say, there were some choices,"},{"time":437201,"text":"but not everything was a matter of choice."},{"time":439226,"text":"And the world we now live in\nlooks like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441385,"text":"[The Ten Commandments DYI Kit]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442985,"text":"And the question is,\nis this good news, or bad news?"},{"time":448000,"text":"And the answer is, \"yes.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":451000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453357,"text":"We all know what's good about it,"},{"time":455487,"text":"so I'm going to talk\nabout what's bad about it."},{"time":458000,"text":"All of this choice has two effects,"},{"time":461471,"text":"two negative effects on people."},{"time":464160,"text":"One effect, paradoxically,"},{"time":466636,"text":"is that it produces paralysis,\nrather than liberation."},{"time":470698,"text":"With so many options to choose from,"},{"time":473000,"text":"people find it very difficult\nto choose at all."},{"time":477293,"text":"I'll give you one very\ndramatic example of this:"},{"time":480000,"text":"a study that was done of investments\nin voluntary retirement plans."},{"time":486109,"text":"A colleague of mine got access\nto investment records from Vanguard,"},{"time":491455,"text":"the gigantic mutual-fund company"},{"time":493100,"text":"of about a million employees\nand about 2,000 different workplaces."},{"time":497000,"text":"And what she found"},{"time":498392,"text":"is that for every 10 mutual funds\nthe employer offered,"},{"time":502684,"text":"rate of participation\nwent down two percent."},{"time":507270,"text":"You offer 50 funds -- 10 percent\nfewer employees participate"},{"time":511522,"text":"than if you only offer five."},{"time":514014,"text":"Why?"},{"time":515197,"text":"Because with 50 funds to choose from,"},{"time":517205,"text":"it's so damn hard to decide\nwhich fund to choose,"},{"time":521000,"text":"that you'll just put it off\nuntil tomorrow."},{"time":523072,"text":"And then tomorrow,"},{"time":524295,"text":"and tomorrow, and tomorrow,"},{"time":526296,"text":"and of course tomorrow never comes."},{"time":528325,"text":"Understand that not only does this mean"},{"time":530478,"text":"that people are going to have\nto eat dog food when they retire"},{"time":533452,"text":"because they don't have\nenough money put away,"},{"time":535658,"text":"it also means that making\nthe decision is so hard"},{"time":538269,"text":"that they pass up significant\nmatching money from the employer."},{"time":542000,"text":"By not participating, they are passing up\nas much as 5,000 dollars a year"},{"time":546000,"text":"from the employer,"},{"time":547321,"text":"who would happily\nmatch their contribution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"So paralysis is a consequence\nof having too many choices."},{"time":553704,"text":"And I think it makes\nthe world look like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556871,"text":"[And lastly, for all eternity,\nFrench, bleu cheese, or ranch?]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":561230,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"You really want to get the decision\nright if it's for all eternity, right?"},{"time":566898,"text":"You don't want to pick the wrong\nmutual fund, or the wrong salad dressing."},{"time":570464,"text":"So that's one effect."},{"time":571640,"text":"The second effect"},{"time":572798,"text":"is that even if we manage to overcome\nthe paralysis and make a choice,"},{"time":578380,"text":"we end up less satisfied\nwith the result of the choice"},{"time":582317,"text":"than we would be if we had\nfewer options to choose from."},{"time":585769,"text":"And there are several reasons for this."},{"time":588362,"text":"One of them"},{"time":589393,"text":"is that with a lot of different\nsalad dressings to choose from,"},{"time":592374,"text":"if you buy one, and it's not perfect --\nand what salad dressing is? --"},{"time":595741,"text":"it's easy to imagine\nyou could have made a different choice"},{"time":598584,"text":"that would have been better."},{"time":600708,"text":"And what happens"},{"time":602000,"text":"is this imagined alternative induces you\nto regret the decision you made,"},{"time":606826,"text":"and this regret subtracts\nfrom the satisfaction"},{"time":609428,"text":"you get out of the decision you made,"},{"time":611230,"text":"even if it was a good decision."},{"time":613610,"text":"The more options there are,\nthe easier it is to regret anything at all"},{"time":617358,"text":"that is disappointing\nabout the option that you chose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":620342,"text":"Second, what economists\ncall \"opportunity costs.\""},{"time":623000,"text":"Dan Gilbert made a big point this morning"},{"time":625000,"text":"of talking about how much the way\nin which we value things"},{"time":630000,"text":"depends on what we compare them to."},{"time":632391,"text":"Well, when there are lots\nof alternatives to consider,"},{"time":636000,"text":"it is easy to imagine\nthe attractive features"},{"time":639179,"text":"of alternatives that you reject"},{"time":642000,"text":"that make you less satisfied\nwith the alternative that you've chosen."},{"time":646657,"text":"Here's an example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647764,"text":"[I can't stop thinking about those other\navailable parking spaces on W 85th street]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":651697,"text":"Sorry if you're not New Yorkers."},{"time":653261,"text":"Here's what you're\nsupposed to be thinking."},{"time":655294,"text":"Here's this couple on the Hamptons."},{"time":657080,"text":"Very expensive real estate."},{"time":658400,"text":"Gorgeous beach. Beautiful day.\nThey have it all to themselves."},{"time":661400,"text":"What could be better?"},{"time":662795,"text":"\"Well, damn it,\" this guy is thinking,"},{"time":664696,"text":"\"It's August. Everybody\nin my Manhattan neighborhood is away."},{"time":668694,"text":"I could be parking\nright in front of my building.\""},{"time":672817,"text":"And he spends two weeks nagged by the idea"},{"time":676436,"text":"that he is missing the opportunity,"},{"time":678314,"text":"day after day, to have\na great parking space."},{"time":683000,"text":"Opportunity costs"},{"time":684419,"text":"subtract from the satisfaction\nwe get out of what we choose,"},{"time":687513,"text":"even when what we choose is terrific."},{"time":690092,"text":"And the more options\nthere are to consider,"},{"time":692171,"text":"the more attractive\nfeatures of these options"},{"time":694401,"text":"are going to be reflected\nby us as opportunity costs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":698197,"text":"Here's another example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":700174,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":703889,"text":"Now this cartoon makes a lot of points."},{"time":706333,"text":"It makes points about living\nin the moment as well,"},{"time":709755,"text":"and probably about doing things slowly."},{"time":711756,"text":"But one point it makes"},{"time":712923,"text":"is that whenever\nyou're choosing one thing,"},{"time":715108,"text":"you're choosing not to do other things"},{"time":717000,"text":"that may have lots of attractive features,"},{"time":719088,"text":"and it's going to make\nwhat you're doing less attractive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":722000,"text":"Third: escalation of expectations."},{"time":724325,"text":"This hit me when I went\nto replace my jeans."},{"time":727230,"text":"I wear jeans almost all the time."},{"time":729531,"text":"There was a time\nwhen jeans came in one flavor,"},{"time":731770,"text":"and you bought them,\nand they fit like crap,"},{"time":733865,"text":"they were incredibly uncomfortable,"},{"time":735579,"text":"if you wore them\nand washed them enough times,"},{"time":738000,"text":"they started to feel OK."},{"time":740000,"text":"I went to replace my jeans after years\nof wearing these old ones,"},{"time":743149,"text":"and I said, \"I want\na pair of jeans. Here's my size.\""},{"time":746024,"text":"And the shopkeeper said,"},{"time":747234,"text":"\"Do you want slim fit,\neasy fit, relaxed fit?"},{"time":750000,"text":"You want button fly or zipper fly?\nYou want stonewashed or acid-washed?"},{"time":753405,"text":"Do you want them distressed?"},{"time":754794,"text":"You want boot cut, tapered, blah blah.\"\nOn and on he went."},{"time":757655,"text":"My jaw dropped."},{"time":759566,"text":"And after I recovered, I said,"},{"time":761090,"text":"\"I want the kind that used\nto be the only kind.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":764288,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"He had no idea what that was,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":771001,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":772182,"text":"so I spent an hour trying on\nall these damn jeans,"},{"time":775000,"text":"and I walked out of the store -- truth! --"},{"time":777071,"text":"with the best-fitting jeans\nI had ever had."},{"time":779736,"text":"I did better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":780919,"text":"All this choice made\nit possible for me to do better."},{"time":784782,"text":"But --"},{"time":785878,"text":"I felt worse."},{"time":788544,"text":"Why? I wrote a whole book\nto try to explain this to myself."},{"time":792000,"text":"The reason --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":793366,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":797745,"text":"The reason I felt worse is that,"},{"time":800000,"text":"with all of these options available,"},{"time":802738,"text":"my expectations about how good\na pair of jeans should be went up."},{"time":809000,"text":"I had very low, no particular expectations\nwhen they only came in one flavor."},{"time":813238,"text":"When they came in 100 flavors, damn it,\none of them should've been perfect."},{"time":816902,"text":"And what I got was good,\nbut it wasn't perfect."},{"time":819263,"text":"And so I compared what I got\nto what I expected,"},{"time":822373,"text":"and what I got was disappointing\nin comparison to what I expected."},{"time":826198,"text":"Adding options to people's lives"},{"time":828262,"text":"can't help but increase\nthe expectations people have"},{"time":831890,"text":"about how good those options will be."},{"time":834000,"text":"And what that's going to produce\nis less satisfaction with results,"},{"time":837215,"text":"even when they're good results."},{"time":839778,"text":"Nobody in the world\nof marketing knows this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842266,"text":"[It all looks so great.\nI can't wait to be disappointed.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":845059,"text":"Because if they did, you wouldn't all know\nwhat this was about."},{"time":848959,"text":"The truth is more like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851521,"text":"[Everything was better back\nwhen everything was worse]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":854614,"text":"The reason that everything was better\nback when everything was worse"},{"time":858650,"text":"is that when everything was worse,"},{"time":860816,"text":"it was actually possible for people"},{"time":862611,"text":"to have experiences\nthat were a pleasant surprise."},{"time":866000,"text":"Nowadays, the world we live in --\nwe affluent, industrialized citizens,"},{"time":870309,"text":"with perfection the expectation --"},{"time":872160,"text":"the best you can ever hope for"},{"time":874065,"text":"is that stuff is as good\nas you expect it to be."},{"time":876754,"text":"You will never be pleasantly surprised"},{"time":878620,"text":"because your expectations,\nmy expectations,"},{"time":880690,"text":"have gone through the roof."},{"time":882063,"text":"The secret to happiness --\nthis is what you all came for --"},{"time":885508,"text":"the secret to happiness"},{"time":888081,"text":"is low expectations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890073,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":893617,"text":"[You'll do]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":894850,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896032,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":899365,"text":"I want to say --"},{"time":900641,"text":"just a little autobiographical moment --"},{"time":903308,"text":"that I actually am married to a wife,"},{"time":906322,"text":"and she's really quite wonderful."},{"time":908000,"text":"I couldn't have done better."},{"time":909598,"text":"I didn't settle."},{"time":911182,"text":"But settling isn't\nalways such a bad thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":914158,"text":"Finally --"},{"time":916080,"text":"One consequence of buying\na bad-fitting pair of jeans"},{"time":919421,"text":"when there is only one kind to buy"},{"time":921493,"text":"is that when you are dissatisfied,\nand you ask why,"},{"time":924000,"text":"who's responsible,"},{"time":925261,"text":"the answer is clear:\nthe world is responsible."},{"time":927793,"text":"What could you do?"},{"time":929410,"text":"When there are hundreds\nof different styles of jeans available,"},{"time":932402,"text":"and you buy one that is disappointing,"},{"time":934798,"text":"and you ask why, who's responsible?"},{"time":937000,"text":"It is equally clear that the answer\nto the question is \"you.\""},{"time":942160,"text":"You could have done better."},{"time":944000,"text":"With a hundred different kinds\nof jeans on display,"},{"time":947000,"text":"there is no excuse for failure."},{"time":949000,"text":"And so when people make decisions,"},{"time":951408,"text":"and even though the results\nof the decisions are good,"},{"time":954000,"text":"they feel disappointed about them;"},{"time":956750,"text":"they blame themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958751,"text":"Clinical depression has exploded"},{"time":960726,"text":"in the industrial world\nin the last generation."},{"time":963241,"text":"I believe a significant -- not the only,\nbut a significant -- contributor"},{"time":967000,"text":"to this explosion of depression,\nand also suicide,"},{"time":970297,"text":"is that people have experiences\nthat are disappointing"},{"time":973000,"text":"because their standards are so high,"},{"time":974882,"text":"and then when they have to explain\nthese experiences to themselves,"},{"time":978098,"text":"they think they're at fault."},{"time":980000,"text":"And so the net result is that we do\nbetter in general, objectively,"},{"time":984000,"text":"and we feel worse."},{"time":987000,"text":"So let me remind you."},{"time":989578,"text":"This is the official dogma,\nthe one that we all take to be true,"},{"time":994000,"text":"and it's all false."},{"time":996641,"text":"It is not true."},{"time":998292,"text":"There's no question that some choice\nis better than none,"},{"time":1002515,"text":"but it doesn't follow from that"},{"time":1004638,"text":"that more choice\nis better than some choice."},{"time":1007000,"text":"There's some magical amount.\nI don't know what it is."},{"time":1009901,"text":"I'm pretty confident that we have\nlong since passed the point"},{"time":1012818,"text":"where options improve our welfare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1015452,"text":"Now, as a policy matter --\nI'm almost done --"},{"time":1018332,"text":"as a policy matter,\nthe thing to think about is this:"},{"time":1021841,"text":"what enables all of this choice"},{"time":1024487,"text":"in industrial societies\nis material affluence."},{"time":1029383,"text":"There are lots of places in the world,"},{"time":1031311,"text":"and we have heard about several of them,"},{"time":1033300,"text":"where their problem\nis not that they have too much choice."},{"time":1036086,"text":"Their problem\nis that they have too little."},{"time":1038208,"text":"So the stuff I'm talking about\nis the peculiar problem"},{"time":1041000,"text":"of modern, affluent, Western societies."},{"time":1044672,"text":"And what is so frustrating\nand infuriating is this:"},{"time":1047921,"text":"Steve Levitt talked to you yesterday"},{"time":1050215,"text":"about how these expensive\nand difficult-to-install child seats"},{"time":1056494,"text":"don't help."},{"time":1058994,"text":"It's a waste of money."},{"time":1060685,"text":"What I'm telling you"},{"time":1061994,"text":"is that these expensive,\ncomplicated choices --"},{"time":1065219,"text":"it's not simply that they don't help."},{"time":1067407,"text":"They actually hurt."},{"time":1069000,"text":"They actually make us worse off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1071928,"text":"If some of what enables\npeople in our societies"},{"time":1075703,"text":"to make all of the choices we make"},{"time":1077726,"text":"were shifted to societies\nin which people have too few options,"},{"time":1082338,"text":"not only would those\npeople's lives be improved,"},{"time":1084642,"text":"but ours would be improved also,"},{"time":1087000,"text":"which is what economists call\na \"Pareto-improving move.\""},{"time":1090001,"text":"Income redistribution will make\neveryone better off --"},{"time":1093737,"text":"not just poor people --"},{"time":1095173,"text":"because of how all this excess\nchoice plagues us."},{"time":1098714,"text":"So to conclude."},{"time":1099786,"text":"[You can be anything\nyou want to be -- no limits]"},{"time":1102120,"text":"You're supposed to read this cartoon,\nand, being a sophisticated person, say,"},{"time":1105783,"text":"\"Ah! What does this fish know?"},{"time":1107262,"text":"You know, nothing is possible\nin this fishbowl.\""},{"time":1110753,"text":"Impoverished imagination,\na myopic view of the world --"},{"time":1113380,"text":"and that's the way I read it at first."},{"time":1115238,"text":"The more I thought about it, however,"},{"time":1117079,"text":"the more I came to the view\nthat this fish knows something."},{"time":1121000,"text":"Because the truth of the matter"},{"time":1123000,"text":"is that if you shatter the fishbowl\nso that everything is possible,"},{"time":1127493,"text":"you don't have freedom."},{"time":1128930,"text":"You have paralysis."},{"time":1131302,"text":"If you shatter this fishbowl\nso that everything is possible,"},{"time":1134493,"text":"you decrease satisfaction."},{"time":1138184,"text":"You increase paralysis,\nand you decrease satisfaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1141780,"text":"Everybody needs a fishbowl."},{"time":1144000,"text":"This one is almost\ncertainly too limited --"},{"time":1146072,"text":"perhaps even for the fish,\ncertainly for us."},{"time":1149333,"text":"But the absence of some metaphorical\nfishbowl is a recipe for misery,"},{"time":1153722,"text":"and, I suspect, disaster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1156000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1157294,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}